SIMPLE: sesquiduplicate
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sesquiduplicate
<hw>Ses`qui*du"pli*cate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Sesqui-</ets> + <ets>duplicate</ets>.]</ety> <def>Twice and a
half as great (as another thing); having the ratio of two and a half to
one.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Sesquiduplicate ratio</b></col> <fld>(Math.)</fld>,
<cd>the ratio of two and a half to one, or one in which the greater term
contains the lesser twice and a half, as that of 50 to 20.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sesquioxide</ent>⟦br⟧
